Norma Mngoma. eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Norma Mngoma is expected to take the stand at the State Capture Inquiry on Monday. The estranged wife of former cabinet minister, Malusi Gigaba is expected to give Gupta related evidence. She will be detailing visits she made with the former minister to the Gupta compound in Saxonwold. READ: State drops all charges against Norma Mngoma Two weeks ago, Mngoma formally withdrew her participation from the Commission, via a letter read by her lawyer. She claimed this was due to the alleged mishandling of her proposed appearance. Before her testimony, her estranged husband Malusi Gigaba is expected to apply to cross-examine her and ask that her evidence be heard in camera.